  "articleSummary": "The article argues that, for cloud‑hosted NVMe SSD storage, Amazon’s EC2 i3 family (especially i3.large and larger) delivers the best price‑to‑performance ratio and the highest overall I/O speed, outperforming other providers and instance types. It backs this claim with head‑to‑head benchmark tables and price comparisons, noting that i3.xlarge is the only instance with competitively priced NVMe capable of >1 GB/s throughput, while network bandwidth often falls short of advertised limits. The piece is written as a practical, data‑driven tutorial for system administrators and DevOps engineers evaluating cloud‑based storage options, using recurring “speed‑vs‑cost” framing and occasional metaphor of “fast‑lane” hardware.",
